race.comment: The 2YO's get us underway and ALL ON RED (1) can keep his unbeaten streak alive. He led and bolted in again with sustained speed last start and his late strength suggests 1100m won't be an issue. Down in weight now after the claim of ZJP and he can make every post a winner yet again. BEATTY (3) has only had one trial coming into his debut, though it was very impressive. The booking of Pike is a positive sign and the inside draw is perfect as he'll be able to lob just off the speed. Can stalk the leaders and get over the top of them late. LONDON ROSE (8) was strong from the back on debut to finish behind ALL ON RED last time out. She'll be better for that experience and she remains down in the weights. Can sit closer this time and put her best foot forward. STAR MARTINI (13) trialled behind BEATTY recently and the inside draw is a big tick. Can feature in the finish. DYNASTIC LASS (11) showed enough on debut and now gets Parnham in the saddle. Include.
